Today's reflection, held together:

On agency — you leaned {locus.dominant}. {locus.dominant === 'internal' ? 'You stayed in the driver\'s seat.' : 'There were moments today where external forces pulled your attention. That\'s worth noticing.'}

On contribution — you showed up {orientation.dominant}. {orientation.dominant === 'contribution' ? 'You gave something today, and that compounded value you won\'t immediately see.' : 'Your attention today was drawn to what you were owed. The question worth sitting with: what would shift if you flipped that?'}

On radius — your circle of concern today was mostly personal. That\'s not wrong — sometimes survival mode is the right mode. But you also said your work benefited you most. Next time you sit down, it\'s worth asking: who else is this for?

Today's reflection, held together:

On agency — you leaned {locus.dominant}. {locus.dominant === 'internal' ? 'You saw your hand in what happened, and that\'s a kind of power.' : 'External circumstances had a grip on today. That\'s real — but somewhere in there you still made choices.'}

On contribution — you showed up {orientation.dominant}. {orientation.dominant === 'contribution' ? 'You gave something without keeping score. That\'s the foundation of trust on any team.' : 'The frustration of not being recognized is real. It\'s also worth asking: what would happen if you contributed first and let the recognition follow?'}

On radius — you were thinking about your team today. You did your work *with* people in mind. That\'s the difference between executing tasks and building something together.

Today's reflection, held together:

On agency — you leaned {locus.dominant}. {locus.dominant === 'internal' ? 'You own your part of today\'s story — the good and the complicated.' : 'Today felt like it happened *to* you in some ways. You still navigated it. That counts.'}

On contribution — you showed up {orientation.dominant}. {orientation.dominant === 'contribution' ? 'You gave something today, and it rippled further than you probably know.' : 'There was some friction today around recognition. Worth asking: who benefits from your work even when no one is watching?'}

On radius — you thought about the people your work actually serves. That\'s rare. Most people never make that connection explicit. When you do, the work changes — and so do you.
